cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CC

This paper deals with the problem of private set intersection, which is a topic in cryptography and privacy-preserving data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves information theory and capacity analysis, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely category. The problem of set intersection involves data structures and algorithms, which could place the paper in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper presents a capacity-achieving scheme, which could be relevant to the field of coding theory and communication complexity, leading to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible category.
